description: Creates a namespace. A namespace is a logical grouping of tables within your table bucket, which you can use to organize tables. For more information, see Create a namespace in the Amazon Simple Storage Service User Guide. You must have the s3tables:CreateNamespace permission to use this operation.

parameters.name: tableBucketARN
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the table bucket to create the namespace in.

nested_items.name: tableBucketARN
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the table bucket the namespace was created in.
